That is an autostart entry, not a desktop shortcut. LXQt reads files like that from ~/.config/autostart/ at login.

If you want Kiddle instead, the same file format applies, just with a different Exec=:

[Desktop Entry]
Type=Application
Name=Firefox ESR Kiddle Kiosk
Exec=sh -c 'mkdir -p /tmp/firefox-kiosk-girls && firefox-esr --no-remote --profile /tmp/firefox-kiosk-girls -kiosk https://www.kiddle.co/'
Terminal=false
OnlyShowIn=LXQt;
X-LXQt-Autostart-enabled=true


